        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 6 at 4:41AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 441 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northeast of Samantha, or 16 miles north of Northport, moving
north at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Whitson, Goodsprings, Boley Springs, Windham Springs, Samantha, West
Corona, Jasper, Cedrum Area, Wiley, Holly Grove, The Wye, Bankhead
Lock And Dam, Tutwiler, Parrish, Oakman, Binion Creek Landing,
Gamble, Corona, Townley, and Cordova.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 AM CDT for central and
west central Alabama.</instruction>
